dcterms:creator: Gordon Christie
Neil Fendley

dcterms:description: A large-scale publicly available remote sensing dataset consisting of approximately 363,571 training images and 53,041 test images across 62 highly granular class categories. It provides images (temporal views) from the same location over time as well as geo-location metadata for each image.
dcterms:title: Functional Map of the World (fMoW)

dcterms:creator: Terrance de Vries
Ishan Misra
Changhan Wang
Laurens van der Maaten
dcterms:description: A geo-tagged subset of ImageNet consisting of 543,435 images with associated coordinates across 5150 class categories. This dataset is more challenging than ImageNet-1k as it is highly imbalanced and contains about 5× more classes.
dcterms:title: GeoImageNet

dcterms:creator: Darius Lam
Richard Kuzma
Kevin McGee
Samuel Dooley
Michael Laielli
Matthew Klaric
Yaroslav Bulatov
Brendan McCord
dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of high resolution satellite images captured with similar sensors to the ones in the fMoW dataset, containing bounding box annotations for 60 different class categories.
dcterms:title: xView

dcterms:creator: Adam Van Etten
Dave Lindenbaum
Todd M Bacastow
dcterms:description: A remote sensing dataset consisting of 5000 high resolution satellite images with segmentation masks for buildings.
dcterms:title: SpaceNet

dcterms:description: High resolution remote sensing images obtained by the USDA’s National Agricultural Imagery Program (NAIP) used for land cover classification across 66 land cover classes.
dcterms:title: NAIP (National Agricultural Imagery Program)
